A MAN appeared in court yesterday accused of threatening to kill Home Secretary Jack Straw and MP Keith Bradley.

James Notley, 47, of Blackburn, Lancs, is alleged to have made the threats to two women at a community centre in the town. He was bailed for two weeks by JPs.


